<section xml:id="section-constructing-the-real-numbers" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>
    Constructing the Real Numbers
  </title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this section, we construct the <term> real number system </term> <m> \R </m> by <term> Dedekind cuts </term>, and we explore the resultant properties of arithmetic and comparison. However, we will find the existence of such a formal construction and its properties more useful than the particular details of the construction itself, and we will shortly leave behind the perspective suggested by our construction.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <xi:include href="./subsection-cutting-the-rational-numbers.ptx"/>

